  "title": "Sales & Marketing",
  "description": "<p><strong></strong></p><h3><strong>Job Description</strong></h3><p>The Sales & Marketing Executive is responsible for managing existing customers, developing new business opportunities, and promoting company products through various marketing channels. This role involves active customer engagement, market expansion, and supporting company sales and branding initiatives.</p><h3><strong>Responsibilities</strong></h3><p>Manage and maintain relationships with existing customers</p><p>Actively source and develop new customers and business opportunities</p><p>Promote products through various online platforms and marketing channels</p><p>Support and execute sales and marketing activities</p><p>Build brand awareness and expand market presence</p><p></p><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><p>Minimum 2 years of relevant sales or marketing experience, or a related qualification/diploma</p><p>Basic computer literacy</p><p>Experience in the beauty industry or related product sales will be an advantage</p><p>Self-motivated, willing to learn, and able to work well in a team</p><p></p><h3><strong>Working Hours</strong></h3><p>Monday to Friday: 9:00 AM – 6:00 PM</p><p>5-day work week</p><p>Required to work 1 Saturday per month</p><p></p><h3><strong>Days Off</strong></h3><p>7 days off per month</p><h3><strong>Work Location</strong></h3><p>Boon Lay</p><h3><strong>Training & Benefits</strong></h3><p>On-the-job training provided</p><p>Structured commission and incentive scheme</p><p>Career advancement opportunities for good performers</p><p>·</p><p></p><h3><strong>Employment Agency Details</strong></h3><p><strong>EA Personnel Name:</strong> Zoe Zhang Zijun<br /><strong>EA Personnel Registration No.:</strong> R23116173<br /><strong>EA Licence No.:</strong> 13C6639</p><p><strong></strong></p>",
